<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=766&amp;p=6685#p6685"><![CDATA[
Most 6502 emulators work instruction-by-instruction, though newer ones are emulating the individual cycles along the way (but not allowing the core to stop in the middle of an instruction) for better synchronization.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Nov 16, 2005 8:57 pm</p><hr />
